thoughts and their feelings

00:01:59.720 --> 00:02:04.880 align:middle line:84%
can affect the physical
activity inside of a quantum

00:02:04.880 --> 00:02:05.850 align:middle line:90%
physics experiment.

00:02:05.850 --> 00:02:07.890 align:middle line:90%
So your mind can affect matter.

00:02:07.890 --> 00:02:09.280 align:middle line:90%
Your mind can affect reality.

00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:10.509 align:middle line:84%
And this is
something people have

00:02:10.509 --> 00:02:12.050 align:middle line:84%
been battling with
trying to understand

00:02:12.050 --> 00:02:14.260 align:middle line:90%
for the last century.

00:02:14.260 --> 00:02:17.500 align:middle line:84%
And they still haven't got to
grips with it, the possibility

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:21.450 align:middle line:84%
that your thoughts could
somehow create reality.

00:02:21.450 --> 00:02:27.140 align:middle line:84%
And I started to look into what
many quantum physicists were

00:02:27.140 --> 00:02:30.410 align:middle line:84%
exploring on how
can we understand

00:02:30.410 --> 00:02:33.120 align:middle line:84%
the role of our thoughts
and feelings and perceptions

00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:34.620 align:middle line:90%
in creating reality.

00:02:34.620 --> 00:02:36.750 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of the
quantum physicists

00:02:36.750 --> 00:02:40.010 align:middle line:84%
would refer to Eastern
philosophies, things

00:02:40.010 --> 00:02:43.930 align:middle line:84%
like Buddhism and Indian
Vedic systems, for example,

00:02:43.930 --> 00:02:45.220 align:middle line:90%
and Taoism.

00:02:45.220 --> 00:02:47.540 align:middle line:84%
It seems that the
models they had

00:02:47.540 --> 00:02:52.470 align:middle line:84%
of how the universe worked that
came from direct perception

00:02:52.470 --> 00:02:56.450 align:middle line:84%
on their medications and so
on, it seemed, bizarrely,

00:02:56.450 --> 00:02:58.750 align:middle line:84%
even though these people had
never been near a particle

00:02:58.750 --> 00:03:01.540 align:middle line:84%
accelerator or a
microscope, they

00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:05.090 align:middle line:84%
seemed to have a remarkable grip
on what was going on at quantum

00:03:05.090 --> 00:03:07.280 align:middle line:90%
levels in the universe.

00:03:07.280 --> 00:03:09.735 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of them got
curious about Buddhism

00:03:09.735 --> 00:03:13.700 align:middle line:84%
and about Vedic
philosophy and Taoism.

00:03:13.700 --> 00:03:16.540 align:middle line:84%
And naturally, I
got interested too.

00:03:16.540 --> 00:03:18.970 align:middle line:84%
I thought, well, if that's where
you get to understand what's

00:03:18.970 --> 00:03:21.750 align:middle line:84%
going on here, then
maybe I need to go over

00:03:21.750 --> 00:03:23.950 align:middle line:90%
there and have a look at it.

00:03:23.950 --> 00:03:28.340 align:middle line:84%
And then a lot of the masters,
these yoga masters and tai

00:03:28.340 --> 00:03:34.610 align:middle line:84%
chi masters, qi gong masters,
they work with energy directly.

00:03:34.610 --> 00:03:36.230 align:middle line:90%
They call it different names.

00:03:36.230 --> 00:03:38.330 align:middle line:84%
In the Indian systems,
they call that prana.

00:03:38.330 --> 00:03:40.800 align:middle line:84%
In the Chinese system,
they call it chi.

00:03:40.800 --> 00:03:43.040 align:middle line:84%
In the Japanese system,
they call it ki.

00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:46.750 align:middle line:84%
But effectively, it's life
force of some kind or other.

00:03:46.750 --> 00:03:49.480 align:middle line:84%
And somehow consciousness,
our thoughts and feelings,

00:03:49.480 --> 00:03:52.660 align:middle line:84%
seems to be in a kind of
collaboration with it.

00:03:52.660 --> 00:03:55.720 align:middle line:84%
So the people who are
the masters in the East,

00:03:55.720 --> 00:03:57.540 align:middle line:84%
they work with
that collaboration.

00:03:57.540 --> 00:03:59.790 align:middle line:84%
They use meditation
to manage their energy

00:03:59.790 --> 00:04:02.530 align:middle line:84%
and their vitality,
especially in things like yoga

00:04:02.530 --> 00:04:04.580 align:middle line:90%
and tai chi and qi gong.

00:04:04.580 --> 00:04:07.030 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, hm,
I'm a physicist,

00:04:07.030 --> 00:04:09.740 align:middle line:84%
but I-- if I could
use my own body

00:04:09.740 --> 00:04:13.575 align:middle line:84%
as an instrument to do
some experimentation, that

00:04:13.575 --> 00:04:14.830 align:middle line:90%
would be really great.

00:04:14.830 --> 00:04:16.940 align:middle line:84%
So I actually went
and studied qi gong

00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:21.339 align:middle line:84%
and I trained in it to
professional levels,

00:04:21.339 --> 00:04:23.465 align:middle line:90%
and also in Chinese medicine.

00:04:23.465 --> 00:04:25.330 align:middle line:84%
I started treating
patients and even

00:04:25.330 --> 00:04:27.640 align:middle line:90%
training other instructors.

00:04:27.640 --> 00:04:31.190 align:middle line:84%
And I started to see
another side to energy.

00:04:31.190 --> 00:04:33.290 align:middle line:84%
There is a physics
side to energy, which

00:04:33.290 --> 00:04:36.110 align:middle line:84%
is all about the way
that energy is perceived

00:04:36.110 --> 00:04:38.660 align:middle line:84%
by particle physicists and
people like Einstein and people

00:04:38.660 --> 00:04:39.880 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:42.120 align:middle line:84%
But then there's this
other side to energy

00:04:42.120 --> 00:04:46.080 align:middle line:84%
which is very different to the
way people look at in the West.

00:04:46.080 --> 00:04:48.820 align:middle line:84%
And it's closely tied
to consciousness.

00:04:48.820 --> 00:04:53.480 align:middle line:84%
So it's like reality, the world
that we live in, in the East,

00:04:53.480 --> 00:04:57.020 align:middle line:84%
they look at it and say,
well, the reality that you're

00:04:57.020 --> 00:05:01.090 align:middle line:84%
experiencing is entirely
dependent on what state of mind

00:05:01.090 --> 00:05:02.590 align:middle line:90%
you're actually in.

00:05:02.590 --> 00:05:07.520 align:middle line:84%
That means that each of us
could be living completely

00:05:07.520 --> 00:05:10.520 align:middle line:84%
different realities based on the
kind of consciousness we're in.

00:05:10.520 --> 00:05:13.310 align:middle line:84%
Though some of us are
asleep, literally,

00:05:13.310 --> 00:05:15.160 align:middle line:84%
or at that level
of consciousness.

00:05:15.160 --> 00:05:19.900 align:middle line:84%
Some of us look like we're
awake from a distance,

00:05:19.900 --> 00:05:22.010 align:middle line:84%
but when you come up close,
you realize they're not--

00:05:22.010 --> 00:05:23.610 align:middle line:90%
that person isn't awake at all.

00:05:23.610 --> 00:05:25.730 align:middle line:84%
They're kind of
sleepwalking, you know?

00:05:25.730 --> 00:05:27.610 align:middle line:84%
And then there are people
who are the highest

00:05:27.610 --> 00:05:29.260 align:middle line:90%
levels of consciousness.

00:05:29.260 --> 00:05:33.880 align:middle line:84%
They are what we might
consider to be called awake.

00:05:33.880 --> 00:05:37.710 align:middle line:84%
And within that there's
different awakening--

00:05:37.710 --> 00:05:38.930 align:middle line:90%
Different degrees.

00:05:38.930 --> 00:05:42.820 align:middle line:84%
But what I found fascinating
was how many people came up

00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:45.520 align:middle line:84%
to me when I first started
discussing this and saying,

00:05:45.520 --> 00:05:47.690 align:middle line:84%
well, OK, that's
a nice philosophy.

00:05:47.690 --> 00:05:50.230 align:middle line:84%
But how do we work
with this practically?

00:05:50.230 --> 00:05:55.270 align:middle line:84%
How do we move from being
asleep to perhaps being awake?

00:05:55.270 --> 00:05:57.690 align:middle line:84%
And how do we know which
of those things we are at,

00:05:57.690 --> 00:05:59.000 align:middle line:90%
you know, in our lives?

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:02.030 align:middle line:84%
What parts of our lives are
asleep, which bits are awake,

00:06:02.030 --> 00:06:04.544 align:middle line:84%
and what parts are we
sleepwalking through?

00:06:04.544 --> 00:06:06.010 align:middle line:84%
And actually, that is
the way to look at it.

00:06:06.010 --> 00:06:08.970 align:middle line:84%
You can't look at a person
say that person is awake

00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:11.660 align:middle line:84%
or that person's asleep or
that person is sleepwalking.

00:06:11.660 --> 00:06:13.797 align:middle line:84%
We're actually a
mixture of those things.

00:06:13.797 --> 00:06:15.130 align:middle line:84%
Our lives are a mixture
of those things.

00:06:15.130 --> 00:06:17.370 align:middle line:84%
Some parts of our
lives are very awake.

00:06:17.370 --> 00:06:19.540 align:middle line:84%
Other parts we're
totally asleep in.

00:06:19.540 --> 00:06:21.350 align:middle line:84%
And there are some where
we think we're awake,

00:06:21.350 --> 00:06:24.520 align:middle line:84%
but actually we're sleepwalking
our way through life.

00:06:24.520 --> 00:06:27.140 align:middle line:84%
And if an incident or something
happens, boom, all of a sudden

00:06:27.140 --> 00:06:32.170 align:middle line:84%
we go back into the
non-awakening state.

00:06:32.170 --> 00:06:37.370 align:middle line:84%
Well, you get some people
who actually have woken up,

00:06:37.370 --> 00:06:38.570 align:middle line:90%
but they don't like it.

00:06:38.570 --> 00:06:40.710 align:middle line:84%
It's uncomfortable for
them to deal with reality

00:06:40.710 --> 00:06:42.180 align:middle line:90%
as it really is.

00:06:42.180 --> 00:06:43.270 align:middle line:90%
You know what they do?

00:06:43.270 --> 00:06:46.960 align:middle line:84%
They actually
choose intentionally

00:06:46.960 --> 00:06:48.480 align:middle line:90%
to go back to sleep.

00:06:48.480 --> 00:06:49.920 align:middle line:90%
They go back to sleep.

00:06:49.920 --> 00:06:52.640 align:middle line:84%
But there's a difference between
people who've woken up and gone

00:06:52.640 --> 00:06:55.050 align:middle line:84%
back to sleep and people
who've never woken up

00:06:55.050 --> 00:06:56.230 align:middle line:90%
and are still asleep.

00:06:56.230 --> 00:06:58.260 align:middle line:84%
Yes, because often we
say you can't go back.

00:06:58.260 --> 00:07:00.547 align:middle line:84%
When you-- once you're asleep,
you awaken, you're awake

00:07:00.547 --> 00:07:03.510 align:middle line:84%
and it's impossible to live
the life you used to live.

00:07:03.510 --> 00:07:05.350 align:middle line:84%
Well, anybody who's
seen the film "Matrix"

00:07:05.350 --> 00:07:07.650 align:middle line:84%
will recognize a
character in there

00:07:07.650 --> 00:07:09.380 align:middle line:84%
who didn't like
the world the way

00:07:09.380 --> 00:07:11.160 align:middle line:84%
it was and he kind
of betrayed all

00:07:11.160 --> 00:07:12.540 align:middle line:90%
the other people in the movie.

00:07:12.540 --> 00:07:14.970 align:middle line:84%
And he decided he just wanted to
be reimplanted back in reality

00:07:14.970 --> 00:07:17.080 align:middle line:84%
as a rich person, and
he wanted to forget

00:07:17.080 --> 00:07:18.680 align:middle line:90%
how reality really was.

00:07:18.680 --> 00:07:19.570 align:middle line:90%
He didn't like it.

00:07:19.570 --> 00:07:21.750 align:middle line:84%
He just wanted to-- he
preferred the illusion.

00:07:21.750 --> 00:07:23.390 align:middle line:90%
The big steak.

00:07:23.390 --> 00:07:24.470 align:middle line:90%
He wanted his meat.

00:07:24.470 --> 00:07:27.130 align:middle line:84%
He liked his steak and he
wanted to be reasonably rich.

00:07:27.130 --> 00:07:29.190 align:middle line:84%
And he didn't care if
it was an illusion.

00:07:29.190 --> 00:07:34.300 align:middle line:84%
To him, it felt better
than the reality.

00:07:34.300 --> 00:07:39.440 align:middle line:84%
So you do get people who-- they
just don't have the capacity

00:07:39.440 --> 00:07:40.280 align:middle line:90%
to deal with the truth.

00:07:40.280 --> 00:07:41.170 align:middle line:90%
It's as simple as that.

00:07:41.170 --> 00:07:42.970 align:middle line:90%
They don't have the capacity.

00:07:42.970 --> 00:07:45.470 align:middle line:84%
So if you're going
to go to a place

00:07:45.470 --> 00:07:47.010 align:middle line:84%
where you are going
to get woken up

00:07:47.010 --> 00:07:49.000 align:middle line:84%
or you're going to
wake yourself up,

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:52.810 align:middle line:84%
you've got to go in with a
caveat, a kind of warning,

00:07:52.810 --> 00:07:57.110 align:middle line:84%
which is, you've got to have the
capacity to deal with the truth

00:07:57.110 --> 00:07:59.820 align:middle line:84%
that you're going to see, that
you're going to experience.

00:07:59.820 --> 00:08:02.250 align:middle line:84%
If you don't have the
capacity to deal with it,

00:08:02.250 --> 00:08:04.080 align:middle line:84%
you're going to go
into a state of shock.

00:08:04.080 --> 00:08:06.150 align:middle line:84%
You're going to go into
such a level of pain

00:08:06.150 --> 00:08:09.640 align:middle line:84%
that you feel permanently
disabled for the rest

00:08:09.640 --> 00:08:10.640 align:middle line:90%
of your life.

00:08:10.640 --> 00:08:14.460 align:middle line:84%
But don't you think that if we
are facing that type of truth,

00:08:14.460 --> 00:08:16.580 align:middle line:84%
then everything being
perfectly in order,

00:08:16.580 --> 00:08:19.980 align:middle line:84%
there is actually the right
moment for us to experience it,

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:21.880 align:middle line:90%
even how bad it can be?

00:08:21.880 --> 00:08:24.150 align:middle line:84%
Like from-- in your own
personal experience,

00:08:24.150 --> 00:08:26.020 align:middle line:84%
maybe that's a
good time to share

00:08:26.020 --> 00:08:27.740 align:middle line:90%
with us what you went through.

00:08:27.740 --> 00:08:32.030 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, and I discovered
something when, a few years

00:08:32.030 --> 00:08:33.947 align:middle line:90%
ago, I end up homeless.

00:08:33.947 --> 00:08:35.380 align:middle line:84%
There were obviously
some truths in my life

00:08:35.380 --> 00:08:38.409 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't facing up to,
otherwise I wouldn't

00:08:38.409 --> 00:08:40.330 align:middle line:90%
have ended up homeless.

00:08:40.330 --> 00:08:44.560 align:middle line:84%
And I discovered something
which I kind of expanded

00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:47.880 align:middle line:90%
upon a scene I saw in a movie.

00:08:47.880 --> 00:08:48.580 align:middle line:90%
I love movies.

