00:09:35.480 --> 00:09:37.525 align:middle line:90%
But the banker is pretty smart.

00:09:37.525 --> 00:09:40.520 align:middle line:84%
And the banker says, look,
before you tell people

00:09:40.520 --> 00:09:43.400 align:middle line:84%
the real truth, you have
to tell them the truth

00:09:43.400 --> 00:09:45.300 align:middle line:90%
that they want to hear.

00:09:45.300 --> 00:09:47.670 align:middle line:84%
And then you're going to
have to tell them the truth

00:09:47.670 --> 00:09:49.540 align:middle line:90%
that they want to believe.

00:09:49.540 --> 00:09:51.330 align:middle line:84%
And only after
that are they even

00:09:51.330 --> 00:09:54.985 align:middle line:84%
going to begin to think about
entertaining the real truth.

00:09:54.985 --> 00:09:56.590 align:middle line:84%
And I thought about
that, you know.

00:09:56.590 --> 00:09:58.190 align:middle line:90%
I thought, he's right.

00:09:58.190 --> 00:10:00.290 align:middle line:84%
I can go to any person
typically in the street,

00:10:00.290 --> 00:10:02.000 align:middle line:84%
and if I just give
them the real truth,

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:04.930 align:middle line:84%
whatever it is, they probably
wouldn't be able to handle it,

00:10:04.930 --> 00:10:05.850 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:10:05.850 --> 00:10:06.960 align:middle line:90%
So I thought--

00:10:06.960 --> 00:10:08.060 align:middle line:84%
They would think
you were crazy.

00:10:08.060 --> 00:10:09.340 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, they'd think I'm crazy.

00:10:09.340 --> 00:10:11.600 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, where
am I coming from?

00:10:11.600 --> 00:10:12.700 align:middle line:84%
And, you know,
that's not the way

00:10:12.700 --> 00:10:14.050 align:middle line:90%
the world is, kind of thing.

00:10:14.050 --> 00:10:16.270 align:middle line:84%
And I thought about
it, I thought, hm.

00:10:16.270 --> 00:10:18.940 align:middle line:84%
So eventually I came
up with a realization

00:10:18.940 --> 00:10:21.840 align:middle line:84%
that before you
can connect people

00:10:21.840 --> 00:10:23.690 align:middle line:84%
to the real truth
about themselves

00:10:23.690 --> 00:10:26.820 align:middle line:84%
and really connect them
into what they really

00:10:26.820 --> 00:10:29.350 align:middle line:84%
need to be woken
up to, they need

00:10:29.350 --> 00:10:35.300 align:middle line:84%
to go to kind of gradual stages
of getting there, to the truth.

00:10:35.300 --> 00:10:38.140 align:middle line:84%
And the first stage is
you have to work with what

00:10:38.140 --> 00:10:41.710 align:middle line:90%
people are willing to hear.

00:10:41.710 --> 00:10:45.190 align:middle line:84%
If you're trying to tell
them that the earth is round

00:10:45.190 --> 00:10:47.120 align:middle line:84%
but that's not what
they're ready to hear,

00:10:47.120 --> 00:10:48.520 align:middle line:84%
as far they're concerned,
they look around

00:10:48.520 --> 00:10:50.960 align:middle line:84%
and everything's flat,
all right, they're not

00:10:50.960 --> 00:10:52.700 align:middle line:90%
going to believe you, you know?

00:10:52.700 --> 00:10:54.030 align:middle line:84%
So the first thing
you've got to do

00:10:54.030 --> 00:10:56.370 align:middle line:84%
is, you've got to
communicate with people

00:10:56.370 --> 00:11:00.160 align:middle line:84%
in their own language,
in the perspectives

00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:03.470 align:middle line:84%
that they're used to and that
are within their experience.

00:11:03.470 --> 00:11:07.110 align:middle line:84%
So you talk to them
only the truths

00:11:07.110 --> 00:11:08.920 align:middle line:84%
that they're already
familiar with,

00:11:08.920 --> 00:11:11.330 align:middle line:90%
that they are prepared to hear.

00:11:11.330 --> 00:11:16.020 align:middle line:84%
And once they know that you are
someone who understands truths

00:11:16.020 --> 00:11:19.240 align:middle line:84%
the way they do, they'll
probably trust you enough

00:11:19.240 --> 00:11:25.090 align:middle line:84%
for you to ask them to consider
other things, things that might

00:11:25.090 --> 00:11:26.970 align:middle line:90%
even challenge their beliefs.

00:11:26.970 --> 00:11:29.480 align:middle line:84%
And that's the next
level of truth.

00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:31.150 align:middle line:84%
Once you tell people
what they want to hear,

00:11:31.150 --> 00:11:32.250 align:middle line:84%
then they're
probably going to be

00:11:32.250 --> 00:11:36.080 align:middle line:84%
ready to be told things which
might shift their beliefs.

00:11:36.080 --> 00:11:38.200 align:middle line:84%
The truth that they're
prepared to believe in

00:11:38.200 --> 00:11:40.300 align:middle line:90%
is about to be shifted.

00:11:40.300 --> 00:11:43.620 align:middle line:84%
And there's a stage where you
get to where people do start

00:11:43.620 --> 00:11:46.130 align:middle line:84%
to change their beliefs,
but you must have told them

00:11:46.130 --> 00:11:48.030 align:middle line:84%
already what they're
prepared to here

00:11:48.030 --> 00:11:51.010 align:middle line:90%
before you even get to there.

00:11:51.010 --> 00:11:53.580 align:middle line:84%
Now, there are a couple of
stages which follow that.

00:11:53.580 --> 00:11:55.490 align:middle line:84%
Once you've told someone
what they want to hear

00:11:55.490 --> 00:11:59.060 align:middle line:84%
and you've told them what
they need to in order for them

00:11:59.060 --> 00:12:01.390 align:middle line:84%
to begin to shift
their beliefs--

00:12:01.390 --> 00:12:03.310 align:middle line:84%
and that's nowhere
near the beginning,

00:12:03.310 --> 00:12:05.240 align:middle line:84%
because they still haven't
changed what they're doing.

00:12:05.240 --> 00:12:07.290 align:middle line:84%
They still haven't changed
the way they're acting.

00:12:07.290 --> 00:12:09.350 align:middle line:84%
So then, once you've
worked with them--

00:12:09.350 --> 00:12:11.170 align:middle line:84%
They start to
question at that stage.

00:12:11.170 --> 00:12:11.900 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, the beliefs.

00:12:11.900 --> 00:12:13.490 align:middle line:84%
If they're shifting
their beliefs,

00:12:13.490 --> 00:12:15.130 align:middle line:84%
they're probably
questioning what's going on,

00:12:15.130 --> 00:12:17.410 align:middle line:84%
and they're wondering whether
what they're doing or acting on

00:12:17.410 --> 00:12:18.860 align:middle line:90%
is the right thing.

00:12:18.860 --> 00:12:20.870 align:middle line:84%
That's usually when
they begin to start

00:12:20.870 --> 00:12:24.070 align:middle line:84%
working with the truth that
changes the way that they act.

00:12:24.070 --> 00:12:26.660 align:middle line:84%
OK, so there's the truth
that they want to hear,

00:12:26.660 --> 00:12:28.930 align:middle line:84%
the truth they want to
believe, then there's the truth

00:12:28.930 --> 00:12:32.440 align:middle line:84%
that they want to-- are prepared
to actually act on and change

00:12:32.440 --> 00:12:33.960 align:middle line:90%
their actions around.

00:12:33.960 --> 00:12:36.640 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, oh, that's
got to be it, that's got

00:12:36.640 --> 00:12:38.020 align:middle line:90%
to be end of it, right?

00:12:38.020 --> 00:12:40.070 align:middle line:84%
But I realized, no, there's
another layer of truth

00:12:40.070 --> 00:12:43.820 align:middle line:84%
beyond that, which is, you
can change the way people act,

00:12:43.820 --> 00:12:46.530 align:middle line:84%
but it doesn't mean that you're
going to change who they are.

00:12:46.530 --> 00:12:49.320 align:middle line:84%
People can pretend
to do stuff, but deep

00:12:49.320 --> 00:12:52.010 align:middle line:84%
down inside of themselves,
they're still the same people.

00:12:52.010 --> 00:12:54.460 align:middle line:84%
They've not changed
who they're being.

00:12:54.460 --> 00:12:58.310 align:middle line:84%
So beyond the truth which
shifts people's beliefs

00:12:58.310 --> 00:13:01.220 align:middle line:84%
is the truth that
shifts who they're

00:13:01.220 --> 00:13:03.770 align:middle line:90%
being, who they actually are.

00:13:03.770 --> 00:13:05.334 align:middle line:84%
So there's all
these layers so far.

00:13:05.334 --> 00:13:06.900 align:middle line:84%
You have to tell people
what they want to hear,

00:13:06.900 --> 00:13:08.566 align:middle line:84%
you have to tell people
what they want to believe,

00:13:08.566 --> 00:13:10.780 align:middle line:84%
you tell people what they're
going to do in order for them

00:13:10.780 --> 00:13:13.420 align:middle line:84%
to change the way the act,
and then, if you're lucky,

00:13:13.420 --> 00:13:15.480 align:middle line:84%
you'll get to the place where
you finally get to change

00:13:15.480 --> 00:13:17.130 align:middle line:90%
who they actually are.

00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:20.020 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, this has surely
got to be the end of it, right?

00:13:20.020 --> 00:13:21.367 align:middle line:84%
This is the final
truth that you're

00:13:21.367 --> 00:13:22.200 align:middle line:90%
going to be working with.

00:13:22.200 --> 00:13:25.630 align:middle line:84%
And I realized, no, of
course it isn't, because

00:13:25.630 --> 00:13:28.490 align:middle line:84%
beyond who we are and
what we think we are

00:13:28.490 --> 00:13:31.040 align:middle line:84%
and what we know
is everything else.

00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:33.294 align:middle line:84%
All the stuff that
we don't know.

00:13:33.294 --> 00:13:34.460 align:middle line:84%
What we don't
know, we don't know.

00:13:34.460 --> 00:13:35.490 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, exactly.

00:13:35.490 --> 00:13:40.060 align:middle line:84%
So there's a truth beyond
what we're prepared to be.

00:13:40.060 --> 00:13:43.580 align:middle line:84%
And that truth, if you'd
like, is the ultimate truth,

00:13:43.580 --> 00:13:45.510 align:middle line:90%
because it's beyond their ego.

00:13:45.510 --> 00:13:46.930 align:middle line:90%
It's beyond our awareness.

00:13:46.930 --> 00:13:48.670 align:middle line:84%
It's beyond what we
think of the world

00:13:48.670 --> 00:13:50.160 align:middle line:90%
and our models of the world.

00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:52.820 align:middle line:84%
It's what exists independently,
whether we are living

00:13:52.820 --> 00:13:54.140 align:middle line:90%
or whether we're dead.

00:13:54.140 --> 00:13:57.450 align:middle line:84%
So it turns out there's five
layers of truth, five levels

00:13:57.450 --> 00:13:59.450 align:middle line:84%
of truth you have to
work with people in order

00:13:59.450 --> 00:14:02.210 align:middle line:84%
for them to become fully
awake, if you like.

00:14:02.210 --> 00:14:05.800 align:middle line:84%
If you're asleep,
then you're probably

00:14:05.800 --> 00:14:08.095 align:middle line:84%
just listening to things
that you're prepared to hear.

00:14:08.095 --> 00:14:10.950 align:middle line:84%
You're not even listen to
things that change your beliefs,

00:14:10.950 --> 00:14:14.840 align:middle line:84%
let alone change the way
you act or who you're being.

00:14:14.840 --> 00:14:18.000 align:middle line:84%
If you are sleepwalking,
then you're

00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:21.370 align:middle line:84%
prepared to at least entertain
some things that people say

00:14:21.370 --> 00:14:23.910 align:middle line:84%
and maybe even change your
beliefs to some degree,

00:14:23.910 --> 00:14:25.520 align:middle line:84%
but you're not going to
change the way you act.

00:14:25.520 --> 00:14:27.960 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to
change who you are.

00:14:27.960 --> 00:14:30.930 align:middle line:84%
And lastly, if you
get to the point

00:14:30.930 --> 00:14:35.200 align:middle line:84%
where you are awake,
what you're hearing

00:14:35.200 --> 00:14:37.760 align:middle line:84%
isn't what you're going
to base your truth on.

00:14:37.760 --> 00:14:41.640 align:middle line:84%
What you believe isn't going to
be what you base your truth on.

00:14:41.640 --> 00:14:44.870 align:middle line:84%
How you act, how someone acts,
you're not going to judge

00:14:44.870 --> 00:14:47.110 align:middle line:90%
a person by the way they act.

00:14:47.110 --> 00:14:51.190 align:middle line:84%
Even who you are, deep down in
terms of the authentic being,

00:14:51.190 --> 00:14:54.970 align:middle line:84%
isn't something that you can
use to gauge how well someone's

00:14:54.970 --> 00:14:57.380 align:middle line:84%
connected to the real truth,
because people who are awake

00:14:57.380 --> 00:15:00.420 align:middle line:84%
know that there's even
a level beyond that.

00:15:00.420 --> 00:15:02.420 align:middle line:84%
So people who are
really awake, they

00:15:02.420 --> 00:15:05.140 align:middle line:90%
can look beyond how people are.

00:15:05.140 --> 00:15:06.970 align:middle line:90%
They can look over time.

00:15:06.970 --> 00:15:10.130 align:middle line:84%
They can look at the long
journey, if you like,

00:15:10.130 --> 00:15:12.930 align:middle line:84%
and they can see that there
might be an ultimate purpose

00:15:12.930 --> 00:15:15.890 align:middle line:84%
which can't be seen right now in
this present moment, that might

00:15:15.890 --> 00:15:17.920 align:middle line:84%
make this person
look bad right now,

00:15:17.920 --> 00:15:20.570 align:middle line:84%
but in the long
sort of journey you

00:15:20.570 --> 00:15:22.760 align:middle line:84%
might see that they're
actually doing some good,

00:15:22.760 --> 00:15:25.050 align:middle line:84%
but nobody gets the
fact that they are.

00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:28.170 align:middle line:84%
So the people who are
awake have some very

00:15:28.170 --> 00:15:30.870 align:middle line:90%
interesting kind of behaviors.

00:15:30.870 --> 00:15:33.230 align:middle line:84%
So I just wanted to
share just two or three

00:15:33.230 --> 00:15:36.290 align:middle line:84%
things about people who are
asleep, people who are awake,

00:15:36.290 --> 00:15:38.460 align:middle line:84%
and people are asleep--
how to spot them,

00:15:38.460 --> 00:15:40.240 align:middle line:84%
how to spot which
of those you are

00:15:40.240 --> 00:15:41.680 align:middle line:84%
and maybe which
parts of your life

00:15:41.680 --> 00:15:43.305 align:middle line:84%
are asleep or awake
or sleepwalking.

00:15:43.305 --> 00:15:45.780 align:middle line:84%
If you can come slightly
closer, because otherwise

00:15:45.780 --> 00:15:47.850 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have this
mike little issue.

00:15:47.850 --> 00:15:50.790 align:middle line:84%
And also I would love to hear
how it is, this is related,

00:15:50.790 --> 00:15:53.700 align:middle line:84%
also I love this parallel
with your own life.

00:15:53.700 --> 00:15:56.300 align:middle line:84%
Because you went
through it big time.

00:15:56.300 --> 00:15:59.750 align:middle line:84%
So at what stage, because you--
I guess we hear it, hear it,

00:15:59.750 --> 00:16:02.540 align:middle line:84%
hear it until we're
really down and suffering

00:16:02.540 --> 00:16:06.000 align:middle line:84%
in this total turmoil to
eventually decide to change,

00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:10.570 align:middle line:84%
but unfortunately it's not
as easy as just hearing it.

00:16:10.570 --> 00:16:13.510 align:middle line:84%
No, part of my life is there
were parts-- there were times

00:16:13.510 --> 00:16:16.510 align:middle line:84%
in my life where I wasn't
prepared to even hear

00:16:16.510 --> 00:16:19.940 align:middle line:84%
and things, let alone shift
my beliefs, the way I acted.

00:16:19.940 --> 00:16:22.060 align:middle line:90%
So I was below asleep.

00:16:22.060 --> 00:16:25.650 align:middle line:84%
I was totally in
a coma in my life.

00:16:25.650 --> 00:16:31.390 align:middle line:84%
And then certain truths hit
me, sometimes in painful ways,

00:16:31.390 --> 00:16:35.710 align:middle line:84%
and you discover that if you
don't change what you believe,

00:16:35.710 --> 00:16:38.410 align:middle line:84%
you're never really going to
act in an appropriate way which

00:16:38.410 --> 00:16:40.260 align:middle line:90%
serves you.

00:16:40.260 --> 00:16:43.210 align:middle line:84%
And many of my
relationships, the kind

00:16:43.210 --> 00:16:47.190 align:middle line:84%
of works that I've done, and
the lessons I've learned,

00:16:47.190 --> 00:16:51.360 align:middle line:84%
they're all about
what level of truth

00:16:51.360 --> 00:16:54.940 align:middle line:84%
do you have the capacity
to work with, you know?

00:16:54.940 --> 00:16:57.620 align:middle line:84%
So one of the things
that I discovered

00:16:57.620 --> 00:17:04.190 align:middle line:84%
was that you need to know
which state you're in.

00:17:04.190 --> 00:17:07.270 align:middle line:84%
And you might find one part
of your life is asleep,

00:17:07.270 --> 00:17:08.640 align:middle line:84%
another part is
awake, and so on.

00:17:08.640 --> 00:17:12.200 align:middle line:84%
But you need to get at
least a map of your life

00:17:12.200 --> 00:17:14.760 align:middle line:84%
and which bits are awake
and which ones are not.

00:17:14.760 --> 00:17:17.530 align:middle line:84%
And you need a way of measuring
whether you're awake or not.

00:17:17.530 --> 00:17:20.721 align:middle line:84%
How do you know whether you're
awake or whether you're asleep?

00:17:20.721 --> 00:17:21.869 align:middle line:90%
Can we even measure it?

00:17:21.869 --> 00:17:24.495 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, how do you
identify whether some part

00:17:24.495 --> 00:17:27.609 align:middle line:84%
of your life or a person that
you know is asleep or a wake.

00:17:27.609 --> 00:17:29.405 align:middle line:84%
And there are
symptoms, you know?

00:17:29.405 --> 00:17:33.200 align:middle line:84%
There are signs which tell
you that person's asleep

00:17:33.200 --> 00:17:35.950 align:middle line:84%
or that part of
my life is asleep.

00:17:35.950 --> 00:17:39.675 align:middle line:84%
That person is awake or that
part of my life is awake.

00:17:39.675 --> 00:17:41.150 align:middle line:84%
Things that we can
spot immediately,

00:17:41.150 --> 00:17:42.270 align:middle line:90%
like having conversation?

00:17:42.270 --> 00:17:43.260 align:middle line:90%
Like what?

00:17:43.260 --> 00:17:45.810 align:middle line:84%
For example, people
who are asleep--

00:17:45.810 --> 00:17:48.880 align:middle line:84%
have you ever tried to talk
to someone who's asleep?

00:17:48.880 --> 00:17:50.070 align:middle line:90%
You can't, right?

00:17:50.070 --> 00:17:51.600 align:middle line:84%
Because they're in
their own little world.

00:17:51.600 --> 00:17:54.720 align:middle line:84%
They don't even probably know
that they're asleep, right?

00:17:54.720 --> 00:17:56.150 align:middle line:84%
And you won't get
a two way dialogue.

00:17:56.150 --> 00:17:58.400 align:middle line:84%
It's like you don't-- I
mean, sometimes I don't even

00:17:58.400 --> 00:17:59.390 align:middle line:90%
hear what they're saying.

00:17:59.390 --> 00:18:01.160 align:middle line:84%
It's a different
resonance, yeah.

00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:03.090 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, they won't hear you.

00:18:03.090 --> 00:18:05.620 align:middle line:84%
It might go in, but you
don't get a response

00:18:05.620 --> 00:18:07.580 align:middle line:84%
from them of the kind
that's linked to what you

00:18:07.580 --> 00:18:08.930 align:middle line:90%
were actually talking about.

00:18:08.930 --> 00:18:10.790 align:middle line:84%
You've probably had
conversations with people

00:18:10.790 --> 00:18:13.250 align:middle line:84%
where you're talking
with them, but they

00:18:13.250 --> 00:18:14.690 align:middle line:84%
seem to be having a
completely different

00:18:14.690 --> 00:18:16.340 align:middle line:90%
conversation from you.

00:18:16.340 --> 00:18:17.690 align:middle line:84%
They just don't
seem to be tuned in

00:18:17.690 --> 00:18:20.110 align:middle line:90%
or present to where you're at.

00:18:20.110 --> 00:18:23.560 align:middle line:84%
So that's often a symptom,
that someone who's asleep

00:18:23.560 --> 00:18:28.100 align:middle line:84%
will often be having their
own little dialogue going on

00:18:28.100 --> 00:18:31.920 align:middle line:84%
and they're not really present
to where you're coming from

00:18:31.920 --> 00:18:35.440 align:middle line:84%
and what you're
trying to communicate.

00:18:35.440 --> 00:18:37.440 align:middle line:84%
Another thing about
people who are asleep

00:18:37.440 --> 00:18:41.240 align:middle line:84%
is often-- you probably heard
stories like this from maybe

00:18:41.240 --> 00:18:43.720 align:middle line:84%
your friends, or I know
there've been occasions

00:18:43.720 --> 00:18:45.730 align:middle line:90%
where I've even done it myself.

00:18:45.730 --> 00:18:47.910 align:middle line:84%
Someone who's asleep, let's
imagine there's a sleepwalker

00:18:47.910 --> 00:18:49.890 align:middle line:90%
who walks all over them.

00:18:49.890 --> 00:18:51.860 align:middle line:84%
Now, the sleepwalker
doesn't even

00:18:51.860 --> 00:18:54.790 align:middle line:84%
know the person who's
asleep is underneath them,

00:18:54.790 --> 00:18:55.890 align:middle line:84%
and they've walked
all over them.

00:18:55.890 --> 00:18:58.010 align:middle line:84%
Now, here's what's
going to happen.

00:18:58.010 --> 00:19:01.560 align:middle line:84%
The person who's asleep, they
don't know that they're asleep,

00:19:01.560 --> 00:19:03.840 align:middle line:84%
and they certainly don't
know that there are people

00:19:03.840 --> 00:19:05.455 align:middle line:84%
in the world like
sleepwalkers or people

00:19:05.455 --> 00:19:07.130 align:middle line:84%
who are awake,
because they don't

00:19:07.130 --> 00:19:10.280 align:middle line:84%
see anything beyond their
own little inner world.

00:19:10.280 --> 00:19:16.190 align:middle line:84%
So if they wake up one day and
they've been hurt and somewhere

00:19:16.190 --> 00:19:17.830 align:middle line:84%
in their life,
sleepwalkers walked

00:19:17.830 --> 00:19:20.330 align:middle line:84%
over them and kicked
them and hurt them,

00:19:20.330 --> 00:19:21.170 align:middle line:90%
they're going to wake up.

00:19:21.170 --> 00:19:23.103 align:middle line:84%
And because they don't know
about the existence of anybody

00:19:23.103 --> 00:19:26.454 align:middle line:84%
else, the person who's asleep
is going to look at their pain,

00:19:26.454 --> 00:19:27.820 align:middle line:84%
they're going to look
at their suffering,

00:19:27.820 --> 00:19:32.110 align:middle line:84%
and they're going to go, well,
must be my fault. I caused it.

00:19:32.110 --> 00:19:33.530 align:middle line:90%
It's my own issue.

00:19:33.530 --> 00:19:35.560 align:middle line:84%
And they'll never
blame anybody else.

00:19:35.560 --> 00:19:38.100 align:middle line:84%
No matter how hard
someone else hurts them,

00:19:38.100 --> 00:19:40.230 align:middle line:84%
they will not
blame anybody else,

00:19:40.230 --> 00:19:41.430 align:middle line:84%
or they will not
have the awareness

00:19:41.430 --> 00:19:44.650 align:middle line:84%
to know that that pain was
caused by somebody else.

00:19:44.650 --> 00:19:46.240 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't self-inflicted.

00:19:46.240 --> 00:19:49.680 align:middle line:84%
But they'll fool themselves
into thinking that they did it

00:19:49.680 --> 00:19:52.190 align:middle line:84%
themselves, that
they're unworthy,

00:19:52.190 --> 00:19:53.880 align:middle line:84%
they're not that
together, they're clumsy,

00:19:53.880 --> 00:19:56.790 align:middle line:84%
or they just don't know
how to handle themselves.

00:19:56.790 --> 00:19:58.260 align:middle line:90%
So they'll blame themselves.

00:19:58.260 --> 00:20:01.190 align:middle line:84%
So that's another symptom of
seeing people who are asleep.

00:20:01.190 --> 00:20:05.310 align:middle line:84%
Other people hurt them,
but they blame themselves.

00:20:05.310 --> 00:20:07.540 align:middle line:84%
So if you are doing that, if
you're beating yourself up

00:20:07.540 --> 00:20:10.460 align:middle line:84%
over something which-- and
you're looking at the pain

00:20:10.460 --> 00:20:12.080 align:middle line:84%
you're experiencing
and you're wondering

00:20:12.080 --> 00:20:15.780 align:middle line:84%
how on earth you did
that to yourself, it

00:20:15.780 --> 00:20:17.350 align:middle line:90%
might be that you never did.

00:20:17.350 --> 00:20:19.845 align:middle line:84%
It might be somebody
else did, and you

00:20:19.845 --> 00:20:21.326 align:middle line:84%
were completely
blind to the fact

00:20:21.326 --> 00:20:23.060 align:middle line:90%
that they were hurting you.

00:20:23.060 --> 00:20:27.760 align:middle line:84%
So these are the are the two
really key symptoms that you

00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:29.680 align:middle line:90%
see of people who are asleep.

00:20:29.680 --> 00:20:31.400 align:middle line:84%
We can definitely
see how we can,

00:20:31.400 --> 00:20:34.490 align:middle line:84%
for example, here can apply
in relationships, and maybe

00:20:34.490 --> 00:20:35.390 align:middle line:90%
not at work.

00:20:35.390 --> 00:20:40.394 align:middle line:84%
Or in relationships, but not
in communications or in--

00:20:40.394 --> 00:20:42.360 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's another feature
about people who are asleep.

00:20:42.360 --> 00:20:44.860 align:middle line:84%
I'll just finish with this
one for people who are asleep.

00:20:44.860 --> 00:20:48.280 align:middle line:90%
Now, imagine you're asleep, OK?

00:20:48.280 --> 00:20:51.980 align:middle line:84%
And the house is burning down
around you that you're in.

00:20:51.980 --> 00:20:55.050 align:middle line:84%
And a fireman bursts through
the doors of the house,

00:20:55.050 --> 00:20:58.810 align:middle line:84%
comes into your bedroom
and violently picks you up

00:20:58.810 --> 00:21:03.030 align:middle line:84%
off the bed and wakes
you up in the process,

00:21:03.030 --> 00:21:04.830 align:middle line:84%
and then begins to take
you down the stairs

00:21:04.830 --> 00:21:06.720 align:middle line:90%
to a place of safety.

00:21:06.720 --> 00:21:08.530 align:middle line:90%
Now, you're asleep.

00:21:08.530 --> 00:21:10.435 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, violently,
you're woken up

00:21:10.435 --> 00:21:13.770 align:middle line:84%
and some strange
person is manhandling

00:21:13.770 --> 00:21:16.470 align:middle line:84%
you and taking you
out while there's

00:21:16.470 --> 00:21:17.920 align:middle line:90%
fire burning around you.

00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:19.100 align:middle line:90%
What are you going to do?

00:21:19.100 --> 00:21:20.621 align:middle line:84%
Are you going to
go, oh, thank you?

00:21:20.621 --> 00:21:21.320 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:21:21.320 --> 00:21:23.200 align:middle line:84%
You're probably going
to start screaming

00:21:23.200 --> 00:21:25.570 align:middle line:84%
and start hitting them, thinking
that you're being kidnapped

00:21:25.570 --> 00:21:27.180 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

00:21:27.180 --> 00:21:30.310 align:middle line:84%
And it isn't until you're out in
the garden, where you're safe,

00:21:30.310 --> 00:21:31.870 align:middle line:84%
and you begin to look
back at your house

00:21:31.870 --> 00:21:34.070 align:middle line:84%
and see it's all burning
down, that you realize

00:21:34.070 --> 00:21:35.830 align:middle line:90%
this person just saved you.

00:21:35.830 --> 00:21:36.540 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:21:36.540 --> 00:21:40.410 align:middle line:84%
So a symptom that you'll
often see is, people who come

00:21:40.410 --> 00:21:42.650 align:middle line:84%
and rescue people who
are asleep and are

00:21:42.650 --> 00:21:45.495 align:middle line:84%
in emergency situations,
the person who's asleep

00:21:45.495 --> 00:21:47.150 align:middle line:90%
will always attack them.

00:21:47.150 --> 00:21:48.400 align:middle line:90%
They'll always beat them up.

00:21:48.400 --> 00:21:51.660 align:middle line:84%
They'll always hurt the
person who's rescuing them.

00:21:51.660 --> 00:21:53.070 align:middle line:84%
Do you know any
people like that?

00:21:53.070 --> 00:21:58.030 align:middle line:84%
People who are being helped in
an emergency situation and they

00:21:58.030 --> 00:21:59.720 align:middle line:84%
don't even know that
they're being helped,

00:21:59.720 --> 00:22:01.470 align:middle line:84%
and they bite the
hand the feeds them?

00:22:01.470 --> 00:22:03.550 align:middle line:84%
They literally fight
them and beat them up.

00:22:03.550 --> 00:22:06.030 align:middle line:84%
And often we reply,
I'm here to help you.

00:22:06.030 --> 00:22:07.370 align:middle line:90%
I'm not here against you.

00:22:07.370 --> 00:22:08.930 align:middle line:84%
Exactly.
Yeah.

00:22:08.930 --> 00:22:12.290 align:middle line:84%
So this is probably
the most stark

00:22:12.290 --> 00:22:15.090 align:middle line:84%
example of someone
who's demonstrating

00:22:15.090 --> 00:22:16.600 align:middle line:90%
a symptom of being asleep.

00:22:16.600 --> 00:22:18.280 align:middle line:84%
They're being rescued
by someone who

00:22:18.280 --> 00:22:20.960 align:middle line:84%
really wants to make
sure they're OK,

00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:22.020 align:middle line:90%
but they just don't see it.

00:22:22.020 --> 00:22:24.940 align:middle line:84%
They think they're
actually being hurt.

00:22:24.940 --> 00:22:27.700 align:middle line:84%
Typically what you see
is that they get taken

00:22:27.700 --> 00:22:29.770 align:middle line:90%
out of a place of comfort.

00:22:29.770 --> 00:22:31.870 align:middle line:84%
They were nice and
comfortable in their bed

00:22:31.870 --> 00:22:33.550 align:middle line:84%
and they've been
taken out of it.

00:22:33.550 --> 00:22:35.960 align:middle line:84%
When a person who's
asleep is taken out

00:22:35.960 --> 00:22:39.740 align:middle line:84%
of a comfort zone in their life
for the sake of their safety

00:22:39.740 --> 00:22:43.700 align:middle line:84%
and to actually ensure that they
are going to survive and not

00:22:43.700 --> 00:22:47.630 align:middle line:84%
die in that comfort zone,
often that individual

00:22:47.630 --> 00:22:50.020 align:middle line:84%
will kick off and
start beating up

00:22:50.020 --> 00:22:52.520 align:middle line:84%
the person who's trying to take
them out that comfort zone.

00:22:52.520 --> 00:22:56.300 align:middle line:84%
They do not like being taken
out of their comfort zone.

00:22:56.300 --> 00:22:57.510 align:middle line:90%
That's what they're used to.

00:22:57.510 --> 00:23:00.510 align:middle line:84%
Addicts are examples
of people are that.

00:23:00.510 --> 00:23:04.210 align:middle line:84%
You try and take someone who's
an addict away from their drugs

00:23:04.210 --> 00:23:07.080 align:middle line:84%
and, you know, the person who's
trying to help that individual

00:23:07.080 --> 00:23:10.200 align:middle line:84%
is clearly trying to get
them away from those drugs.

00:23:10.200 --> 00:23:12.505 align:middle line:84%
But the person who's got
the drugs and is an addict,

00:23:12.505 --> 00:23:14.320 align:middle line:90%
he won't look at it that way.

00:23:14.320 --> 00:23:16.000 align:middle line:84%
He'll think you're
taking away something

00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:18.030 align:middle line:90%
that's vital for his survival.

00:23:18.030 --> 00:23:19.650 align:middle line:84%
And he will kick,
he will scream,

00:23:19.650 --> 00:23:24.700 align:middle line:84%
they even do things like rob and
kill just so they can sustain

00:23:24.700 --> 00:23:26.410 align:middle line:90%
being in that comfort zone.

00:23:26.410 --> 00:23:27.440 align:middle line:90%
They do that.

00:23:27.440 --> 00:23:29.830 align:middle line:84%
And that exists too
for soft addictions.

00:23:29.830 --> 00:23:32.570 align:middle line:84%
Some people are addicted to
shopping or internet or what

00:23:32.570 --> 00:23:37.280 align:middle line:84%
have you, and we-- it can
unleash the worst of ourselves

00:23:37.280 --> 00:23:40.930 align:middle line:84%
when we're confronted and
when somebody takes that away.

00:23:40.930 --> 00:23:42.290 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's an
example of someone

00:23:42.290 --> 00:23:45.040 align:middle line:90%
who's kind of half asleep.

00:23:45.040 --> 00:23:49.890 align:middle line:84%
Because they're kind of
sleepwalking, if you like.

00:23:49.890 --> 00:23:52.490 align:middle line:84%
And here's the thing
about sleepwalkers.

00:23:52.490 --> 00:23:55.600 align:middle line:84%
Sleepwalkers, from a distance,
you can imagine seeing them

00:23:55.600 --> 00:23:57.761 align:middle line:84%
in a room and they're
making themselves a cup

00:23:57.761 --> 00:23:59.640 align:middle line:90%
of tea or whatever, all right?

00:23:59.640 --> 00:24:02.390 align:middle line:84%
And you walk into the room
and you see them doing this.

00:24:02.390 --> 00:24:04.180 align:middle line:84%
If you see someone like
that in a room doing

00:24:04.180 --> 00:24:06.770 align:middle line:84%
that kind of thing,
you clearly would not

00:24:06.770 --> 00:24:08.630 align:middle line:90%
think that they were asleep.

00:24:08.630 --> 00:24:10.780 align:middle line:84%
You would think, well,
that person must be awake.

00:24:10.780 --> 00:24:13.290 align:middle line:84%
They're making
themselves a cup of tea.

00:24:13.290 --> 00:24:15.940 align:middle line:84%
So you walk over to them
thinking that they're awake--

00:24:15.940 --> 00:24:18.280 align:middle line:90%
Where is this going?

00:24:18.280 --> 00:24:20.520 align:middle line:84%
And you try to have a
conversation with them

00:24:20.520 --> 00:24:22.270 align:middle line:90%
and they won't respond to you.

00:24:22.270 --> 00:24:24.540 align:middle line:84%
They keep making their cup
of tea, wandering around,

00:24:24.540 --> 00:24:27.850 align:middle line:84%
and they somehow, they
can't see your presence.

00:24:27.850 --> 00:24:30.500 align:middle line:84%
They can't even see
that you're there.

00:24:30.500 --> 00:24:32.930 align:middle line:84%
And it's quite strange,
because from a distance,

00:24:32.930 --> 00:24:35.860 align:middle line:84%
they look like they're awake,
but then when you get up close

00:24:35.860 --> 00:24:39.150 align:middle line:84%
to them and you try and have
a conversation or a dialogue

00:24:39.150 --> 00:24:42.670 align:middle line:84%
or try make a connection,
it just doesn't happen.

00:24:42.670 --> 00:24:44.840 align:middle line:84%
And you probably are aware
of people, when you first

00:24:44.840 --> 00:24:47.295 align:middle line:84%
met them, you thought, wow,
this person's really bright,

00:24:47.295 --> 00:24:49.550 align:middle line:84%
they're really awake,
they're really tuned in.

00:24:49.550 --> 00:24:51.440 align:middle line:84%
And then, as you
get to know them,

00:24:51.440 --> 00:24:54.520 align:middle line:84%
you realize it was all a
pretty superficial thing

00:24:54.520 --> 00:24:57.340 align:middle line:84%
and that deep down
within themselves, they

00:24:57.340 --> 00:24:58.847 align:middle line:90%
aren't awake at all.

00:24:58.847 --> 00:24:59.980 align:middle line:84%
They're completely
blind to what's

00:24:59.980 --> 00:25:04.130 align:middle line:84%
going on in their lives and
it's kind of a facade, almost.

00:25:04.130 --> 00:25:07.200 align:middle line:84%
And often they're the
kind of people, again,

00:25:07.200 --> 00:25:10.110 align:middle line:84%
there are symptoms to
spot people like that.

00:25:10.110 --> 00:25:13.930 align:middle line:84%
So one of the symptoms is often
they'll hurt people and not

00:25:13.930 --> 00:25:16.490 align:middle line:90%
even know they're doing it.

00:25:16.490 --> 00:25:19.100 align:middle line:84%
It's only when they wake
up and someone tells them,

00:25:19.100 --> 00:25:20.600 align:middle line:84%
did you realize you were
hurting that person?

00:25:20.600 --> 00:25:23.800 align:middle line:84%
And the person usually goes,
I had no idea I had no idea

00:25:23.800 --> 00:25:25.200 align:middle line:90%
I was hurting that person.

00:25:25.200 --> 00:25:26.580 align:middle line:90%
And this is what you'll see.

00:25:26.580 --> 00:25:28.570 align:middle line:84%
Someone who's
sleepwalking, for example,

00:25:28.570 --> 00:25:31.830 align:middle line:84%
will very casually walk
over somebody who's asleep,

00:25:31.830 --> 00:25:34.230 align:middle line:90%
for example, and hurt them.

00:25:34.230 --> 00:25:37.100 align:middle line:84%
And while they're doing it,
because they're sleepwalking,

00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:39.694 align:middle line:84%
they won't even know that
that person was there.

00:25:39.694 --> 00:25:40.860 align:middle line:84%
They won't even
know that they hurt

00:25:40.860 --> 00:25:43.010 align:middle line:90%
them through their actions.

00:25:43.010 --> 00:25:46.410 align:middle line:84%
And it's only when they
wake up, truly wake up,

00:25:46.410 --> 00:25:49.260 align:middle line:84%
and someone who's awake
says, that person over there,

00:25:49.260 --> 00:25:51.260 align:middle line:84%
do you realize you
walked all over them?

00:25:51.260 --> 00:25:53.290 align:middle line:84%
That you took advantage of
them, that you hurt them?

00:25:53.290 --> 00:25:55.770 align:middle line:84%
And the person who was
sleepwalking and is now awake

00:25:55.770 --> 00:25:57.480 align:middle line:90%
will go, I had no idea.

00:25:57.480 --> 00:25:59.280 align:middle line:90%
I'd no idea I'd hurt them.

00:25:59.280 --> 00:26:04.910 align:middle line:84%
And if I was-- if I'd known,
I wouldn't have done that.

00:26:04.910 --> 00:26:07.370 align:middle line:84%
So often people who
are sleepwalkers only

00:26:07.370 --> 00:26:11.320 align:middle line:84%
discover that they've hurt
people when they've woken up

00:26:11.320 --> 00:26:15.270 align:middle line:84%
because some dramatic event
has happened in their lives

00:26:15.270 --> 00:26:19.600 align:middle line:84%
or someone who's
genuinely awake and wise

00:26:19.600 --> 00:26:21.660 align:middle line:84%
draws their attention
to something.

00:26:21.660 --> 00:26:24.190 align:middle line:84%
And they get to see that
they've hurt someone

00:26:24.190 --> 00:26:26.940 align:middle line:84%
and they didn't even know
that they've been doing it.

00:26:26.940 --> 00:26:30.300 align:middle line:84%
So hurting other people without
knowing that you're doing it

00:26:30.300 --> 00:26:34.030 align:middle line:84%
is often a symptom of
someone who's sleepwalking.

00:26:34.030 --> 00:26:37.190 align:middle line:84%
There are a couple of other
symptoms, and one of the ones

00:26:37.190 --> 00:26:42.820 align:middle line:84%
is that someone
who's sleepwalking,

00:26:42.820 --> 00:26:45.314 align:middle line:84%
like the person
who's asleep, there's

00:26:45.314 --> 00:26:46.180 align:middle line:90%
an issue with eye contact.

00:26:46.180 --> 00:26:49.080 align:middle line:90%


00:26:49.080 --> 00:26:50.530 align:middle line:84%
Someone who's
sleepwalking, they will

00:26:50.530 --> 00:26:52.250 align:middle line:90%
be living in their own world.

00:26:52.250 --> 00:26:54.900 align:middle line:84%
You can stare at them
straight in the face

00:26:54.900 --> 00:26:58.290 align:middle line:84%
and they won't see you there,
and they'll carry on doing

00:26:58.290 --> 00:27:00.110 align:middle line:90%
things that they were doing.

00:27:00.110 --> 00:27:04.680 align:middle line:84%
So you might have a direct
connection with this person,

00:27:04.680 --> 00:27:06.400 align:middle line:84%
right, and you
think that you had

00:27:06.400 --> 00:27:08.420 align:middle line:84%
a direct connection
with that person,

00:27:08.420 --> 00:27:11.240 align:middle line:84%
but somehow it was
all an illusion.

00:27:11.240 --> 00:27:12.230 align:middle line:90%
They were never really there.

00:27:12.230 --> 00:27:14.790 align:middle line:90%


00:27:14.790 --> 00:27:16.280 align:middle line:90%
You can see in the eyes, no?

00:27:16.280 --> 00:27:18.361 align:middle line:84%
Literally, you can
see it in the eyes.

00:27:18.361 --> 00:27:19.060 align:middle line:90%
You thought--

00:27:19.060 --> 00:27:21.790 align:middle line:84%
A bit scary for an
awakened person to see that.

00:27:21.790 --> 00:27:24.600 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, because you thought
from a distance that person

00:27:24.600 --> 00:27:26.230 align:middle line:84%
was awake, so you're
looking forward

00:27:26.230 --> 00:27:27.830 align:middle line:84%
to going over, having
a conversation,

00:27:27.830 --> 00:27:29.040 align:middle line:90%
and doing things with them.

00:27:29.040 --> 00:27:31.510 align:middle line:84%
And then when you get
there, you find you

00:27:31.510 --> 00:27:32.770 align:middle line:90%
can't do anything with them.

00:27:32.770 --> 00:27:35.440 align:middle line:84%
They're on their
own little mission.

00:27:35.440 --> 00:27:39.310 align:middle line:84%
They're not even aware of your
presence, your true presence,

00:27:39.310 --> 00:27:41.780 align:middle line:90%
where you're really from.

00:27:41.780 --> 00:27:45.080 align:middle line:84%
So sleepwalkers do
have these symptoms.

00:27:45.080 --> 00:27:47.840 align:middle line:84%
But the most amazing thing,
the most amazing thing

00:27:47.840 --> 00:27:52.150 align:middle line:90%
is people who are awake.

00:27:52.150 --> 00:27:55.590 align:middle line:84%
People who are
awake-- imagine seeing

00:27:55.590 --> 00:27:58.360 align:middle line:90%
someone who's awake in a room.

00:27:58.360 --> 00:28:01.130 align:middle line:84%
If they see you across the
room-- one of the things

00:28:01.130 --> 00:28:05.750 align:middle line:84%
that people typically will do is
they'll acknowledge you, right?

00:28:05.750 --> 00:28:08.320 align:middle line:84%
They'll at least maintain
eye contact with you,

00:28:08.320 --> 00:28:10.230 align:middle line:84%
and that's a kind
of acknowledgement.

00:28:10.230 --> 00:28:12.600 align:middle line:84%
They recognize that
you exist and they

00:28:12.600 --> 00:28:14.490 align:middle line:90%
spotted you in the room, right?

00:28:14.490 --> 00:28:17.860 align:middle line:84%
So maintaining eye contact
is one of the things

00:28:17.860 --> 00:28:19.880 align:middle line:84%
that people who are
awake actually do.

00:28:19.880 --> 00:28:23.000 align:middle line:84%
It's not absolute thing,
but it's a thing that people

00:28:23.000 --> 00:28:24.485 align:middle line:90%
who are awake actually do.

00:28:24.485 --> 00:28:26.560 align:middle line:84%
Now, the other thing
that someone who's awake

00:28:26.560 --> 00:28:33.210 align:middle line:84%
actually does is someone who's
awake can see who's asleep

00:28:33.210 --> 00:28:35.540 align:middle line:84%
and they can see
who's sleepwalking.

00:28:35.540 --> 00:28:38.320 align:middle line:84%
Once they get up close enough,
they can see that that person's

00:28:38.320 --> 00:28:39.520 align:middle line:90%
sleepwalking.

00:28:39.520 --> 00:28:42.250 align:middle line:84%
The other thing that a
person who's awake can do

00:28:42.250 --> 00:28:50.090 align:middle line:84%
is that they can make plans
with other people who are awake.

00:28:50.090 --> 00:28:51.980 align:middle line:84%
A person who's awake
can't make plans

00:28:51.980 --> 00:28:53.960 align:middle line:90%
with someone who's asleep.

00:28:53.960 --> 00:28:56.260 align:middle line:84%
They can sit there by the
bed and go through all

00:28:56.260 --> 00:28:57.740 align:middle line:84%
these options, and
the person is not

00:28:57.740 --> 00:29:00.600 align:middle line:84%
going to be able to contribute
at all to making those plans.

00:29:00.600 --> 00:29:02.560 align:middle line:84%
And a sleepwalker isn't going
to be able to contribute

00:29:02.560 --> 00:29:04.100 align:middle line:90%
to making your plans either.

00:29:04.100 --> 00:29:09.200 align:middle line:84%
The only person you make plans
with or some kind of goal

00:29:09.200 --> 00:29:11.050 align:middle line:84%
that you want to commonly
achieve between--

00:29:11.050 --> 00:29:12.160 align:middle line:90%
Big plans.

00:29:12.160 --> 00:29:13.700 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, big plans.

00:29:13.700 --> 00:29:15.690 align:middle line:90%
The people who are awake.

00:29:15.690 --> 00:29:18.210 align:middle line:84%
You can only make big
plans, in other words,

00:29:18.210 --> 00:29:20.940 align:middle line:90%
with people who are awake.

00:29:20.940 --> 00:29:23.020 align:middle line:90%
It's safer, too, probably.

00:29:23.020 --> 00:29:25.680 align:middle line:84%
Well, what you'll find is
that people who are awake,

00:29:25.680 --> 00:29:29.230 align:middle line:84%
they'll end up in a two-way
conversation with you.

00:29:29.230 --> 00:29:30.870 align:middle line:90%
It's not a one-way conversation.

00:29:30.870 --> 00:29:33.180 align:middle line:84%
You talk to someone who's
asleep or a sleepwalker,

00:29:33.180 --> 00:29:35.200 align:middle line:84%
you're the one who's
doing all the talking.

00:29:35.200 --> 00:29:38.730 align:middle line:84%
And the other person, they're
either not responding at all

00:29:38.730 --> 00:29:40.020 align:middle line:84%
or they're just
going about doing

00:29:40.020 --> 00:29:42.400 align:middle line:90%
stuff as if you're not there.

00:29:42.400 --> 00:29:45.520 align:middle line:84%
A person who's awake
will listen to you

00:29:45.520 --> 00:29:48.450 align:middle line:84%
and will feed back things
to you based on the things

00:29:48.450 --> 00:29:49.670 align:middle line:90%
that you've been saying.

00:29:49.670 --> 00:29:51.840 align:middle line:84%
And maybe between
yourselves, you

00:29:51.840 --> 00:29:54.830 align:middle line:84%
can come up with a plan to help
the sleepwalkers to stop them

00:29:54.830 --> 00:29:57.840 align:middle line:84%
from waling all
over the sleepers.

00:29:57.840 --> 00:30:02.160 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you can do something which
ensures that the people who are

00:30:02.160 --> 00:30:04.880 align:middle line:84%
asleep don't roll off
the edge of a cliff

00:30:04.880 --> 00:30:07.540 align:middle line:90%
in the middle of their sleep.

00:30:07.540 --> 00:30:11.220 align:middle line:84%
So the people who are awake,
they can do all these things.

00:30:11.220 --> 00:30:13.390 align:middle line:84%
But the thing I love about
the people who are awake

00:30:13.390 --> 00:30:18.560 align:middle line:84%
is that if they're
strong enough, then

00:30:18.560 --> 00:30:21.840 align:middle line:84%
they can be there for the
sleepwalkers and the people who

00:30:21.840 --> 00:30:25.130 align:middle line:90%
are asleep when they wake up.

00:30:25.130 --> 00:30:26.680 align:middle line:84%
If you imagine
you've been asleep

00:30:26.680 --> 00:30:29.830 align:middle line:84%
and you're just beginning to
wake up and rubbing your eyes

00:30:29.830 --> 00:30:33.140 align:middle line:84%
and stretching open, looking
at the world around you,

00:30:33.140 --> 00:30:36.280 align:middle line:84%
and thinking, where
am I, kind of thing,

00:30:36.280 --> 00:30:40.010 align:middle line:84%
it's great to have someone
who's awake there by your side

00:30:40.010 --> 00:30:41.170 align:middle line:90%
when you wake up.

00:30:41.170 --> 00:30:44.220 align:middle line:84%
Because they can tell you,
oh, by the way, those things

00:30:44.220 --> 00:30:46.450 align:middle line:90%
down there, they're your legs.

00:30:46.450 --> 00:30:49.260 align:middle line:84%
You're going to need those
to get around this world.

00:30:49.260 --> 00:30:52.040 align:middle line:84%
And if you want to
get rid of stuff

00:30:52.040 --> 00:30:54.460 align:middle line:84%
that you don't need any more,
you want to dump garbage

00:30:54.460 --> 00:30:57.500 align:middle line:84%
from your past, baggage, there's
a spiritual toilet over there,

00:30:57.500 --> 00:30:58.200 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:30:58.200 --> 00:31:00.020 align:middle line:84%
That's where you go
and let go of stuff

00:31:00.020 --> 00:31:01.440 align:middle line:90%
that you don't need any more.

00:31:01.440 --> 00:31:02.650 align:middle line:84%
There's a kitchen
over there where

00:31:02.650 --> 00:31:03.920 align:middle line:90%
you can go nurture yourself.

00:31:03.920 --> 00:31:08.410 align:middle line:84%
And those people over
there, don't disturb them.

00:31:08.410 --> 00:31:11.360 align:middle line:84%
They are in a deep
state of meditation

00:31:11.360 --> 00:31:14.520 align:middle line:84%
and they're trying to awaken
to an even higher level.

00:31:14.520 --> 00:31:17.930 align:middle line:84%
Have you come across
people who, people have

00:31:17.930 --> 00:31:20.520 align:middle line:84%
told you this
person's really awake,

00:31:20.520 --> 00:31:23.440 align:middle line:90%
they're kind of enlightened?

00:31:23.440 --> 00:31:26.230 align:middle line:84%
Yet when you go and approach
them, they kind of reject you,

00:31:26.230 --> 00:31:29.060 align:middle line:84%
they tell you, no, don't
talk to me, go away.

00:31:29.060 --> 00:31:30.700 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever come
across people like that?

00:31:30.700 --> 00:31:33.540 align:middle line:84%
I've met a lot of
spiritual egos, yeah.

00:31:33.540 --> 00:31:37.180 align:middle line:84%
Some people that they
were, but talking to them,

00:31:37.180 --> 00:31:40.490 align:middle line:84%
and actually then I decide not
to post those videos online,

00:31:40.490 --> 00:31:42.720 align:middle line:84%
because it doesn't
feel right, yeah.

00:31:42.720 --> 00:31:45.270 align:middle line:84%
Well, there are certain
individuals who actually are

00:31:45.270 --> 00:31:49.045 align:middle line:84%
very awake, but they're
trying to do a service for all

00:31:49.045 --> 00:31:50.670 align:middle line:90%
the people who are awake.

00:31:50.670 --> 00:31:52.687 align:middle line:90%
They're doing a higher service.

00:31:52.687 --> 00:31:53.920 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of the
people who are awake

00:31:53.920 --> 00:31:57.240 align:middle line:84%
will tell you, don't
interfere with that person.

00:31:57.240 --> 00:32:00.150 align:middle line:84%
They're doing something
to enable us to even wake

00:32:00.150 --> 00:32:02.050 align:middle line:90%
up to an even higher level.

00:32:02.050 --> 00:32:06.750 align:middle line:84%
And that means they can't
afford to spend time doing

00:32:06.750 --> 00:32:09.640 align:middle line:84%
trivial things like
just helping you gab it,

00:32:09.640 --> 00:32:11.590 align:middle line:84%
you know, in terms
of wakefulness.

00:32:11.590 --> 00:32:14.730 align:middle line:84%
And compassionately,
those individuals,

00:32:14.730 --> 00:32:16.130 align:middle line:84%
when you approach
them and you see

00:32:16.130 --> 00:32:18.010 align:middle line:84%
what a great source
of light they are,

00:32:18.010 --> 00:32:21.130 align:middle line:84%
compassionately, they
will indicate to you

00:32:21.130 --> 00:32:23.705 align:middle line:84%
they're not
available to help you

00:32:23.705 --> 00:32:26.510 align:middle line:84%
and you need to find
somebody else who's awake

00:32:26.510 --> 00:32:30.120 align:middle line:84%
and who isn't committed to
such a task as they are.

00:32:30.120 --> 00:32:31.510 align:middle line:84%
And I've come across
people like that.

00:32:31.510 --> 00:32:33.830 align:middle line:84%
I've come across
people who everybody

00:32:33.830 --> 00:32:36.310 align:middle line:84%
else said, oh, that's the
person you should go to.

00:32:36.310 --> 00:32:38.800 align:middle line:84%
And I've gone there
and I found that they

00:32:38.800 --> 00:32:43.000 align:middle line:84%
weren't as accommodating
as I thought they would be.

00:32:43.000 --> 00:32:48.635 align:middle line:84%
And in the end I realized, oh,
that person was someone who

00:32:48.635 --> 00:32:50.810 align:middle line:84%
used to help
people, but his role

00:32:50.810 --> 00:32:53.030 align:middle line:90%
has changed now in this world.

00:32:53.030 --> 00:32:57.080 align:middle line:84%
He's now dealing with
higher duties, if you like.

00:32:57.080 --> 00:32:59.210 align:middle line:84%
Therefore he's not someone
I should be bothering,

00:32:59.210 --> 00:33:00.340 align:middle line:90%
you know, out of respect.

00:33:00.340 --> 00:33:02.160 align:middle line:84%
You should leave them alone
because they're dealing

00:33:02.160 --> 00:33:03.555 align:middle line:90%
with a big-- bigger things.

00:33:03.555 --> 00:33:06.190 align:middle line:90%
But often we misplace that.

00:33:06.190 --> 00:33:08.775 align:middle line:84%
Because I hear so
often, I receive a lot

00:33:08.775 --> 00:33:10.960 align:middle line:90%
of feedbacks from the internet.

00:33:10.960 --> 00:33:14.160 align:middle line:84%
And often people say oh, this
person used to be available

00:33:14.160 --> 00:33:18.750 align:middle line:84%
but is not any more, and
he's just a different person.

00:33:18.750 --> 00:33:20.290 align:middle line:90%
He has changed.

00:33:20.290 --> 00:33:22.540 align:middle line:84%
It's not anymore that
leader, that person

00:33:22.540 --> 00:33:23.740 align:middle line:90%
that I used to know.

00:33:23.740 --> 00:33:26.300 align:middle line:84%
It's immediately we
feel then the separation

00:33:26.300 --> 00:33:27.370 align:middle line:90%
when it's not personal.

00:33:27.370 --> 00:33:29.340 align:middle line:90%
No, it's not personal.

00:33:29.340 --> 00:33:31.790 align:middle line:84%
It's just they've got
a bigger duty than us.

00:33:31.790 --> 00:33:34.410 align:middle line:84%
Now, you do get people
who are egotistical,

00:33:34.410 --> 00:33:36.680 align:middle line:90%
who used to help people.

00:33:36.680 --> 00:33:39.370 align:middle line:84%
But because they failed
to honor themselves

00:33:39.370 --> 00:33:41.870 align:middle line:84%
in the process of
helping others,

00:33:41.870 --> 00:33:44.640 align:middle line:84%
they ran themselves down and
they're not in a position,

00:33:44.640 --> 00:33:46.710 align:middle line:84%
energetically, to
have the capacity

00:33:46.710 --> 00:33:48.260 align:middle line:90%
to help anybody else any more.

00:33:48.260 --> 00:33:50.210 align:middle line:84%
So when people come to
them because they've

00:33:50.210 --> 00:33:52.150 align:middle line:84%
heard all these tales
about this person

00:33:52.150 --> 00:33:54.540 align:middle line:84%
and then that
particular master just

00:33:54.540 --> 00:33:57.884 align:middle line:84%
shoves them away and pushes them
away, people don't understand.

00:33:57.884 --> 00:33:59.150 align:middle line:84%
You're supposed to
be a master, you're

00:33:59.150 --> 00:34:01.410 align:middle line:84%
supposed to be a guru,
dut dah duh duh duh duh.

00:34:01.410 --> 00:34:03.940 align:middle line:84%
Yet you're rejecting me,
you're being horrible to me,

00:34:03.940 --> 00:34:04.950 align:middle line:90%
dah duh dah duh dah.

00:34:04.950 --> 00:34:07.850 align:middle line:84%
And it's because
that person was never

00:34:07.850 --> 00:34:09.790 align:middle line:90%
a master in the first place.

00:34:09.790 --> 00:34:13.270 align:middle line:84%
They put themselves out
as someone who could help.

00:34:13.270 --> 00:34:17.150 align:middle line:84%
Other people, maybe, made
that person into a master,

00:34:17.150 --> 00:34:19.560 align:middle line:84%
and it was a role
they never wanted.

00:34:19.560 --> 00:34:21.110 align:middle line:90%
They just had a gift.

00:34:21.110 --> 00:34:22.960 align:middle line:84%
They chose to share
it with people.

00:34:22.960 --> 00:34:24.929 align:middle line:84%
Too many people
demanded it from them

00:34:24.929 --> 00:34:27.530 align:middle line:84%
and they didn't-- he didn't
have enough left for himself.

00:34:27.530 --> 00:34:29.790 align:middle line:84%
And as a consequence
he ran himself down,

00:34:29.790 --> 00:34:32.350 align:middle line:84%
and the next thing you know,
he isn't available for anybody

00:34:32.350 --> 00:34:33.310 align:middle line:90%
any more.

00:34:33.310 --> 00:34:35.555 align:middle line:84%
Now I had someone
who was a mas--

00:34:35.555 --> 00:34:37.589 align:middle line:90%
I worked for who was like that.

00:34:37.589 --> 00:34:40.620 align:middle line:84%
But there's also some people
that think they have it or they

00:34:40.620 --> 00:34:43.129 align:middle line:90%
think they're-- and they don't.

00:34:43.129 --> 00:34:48.090 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's also
disillusion within this realm.

00:34:48.090 --> 00:34:53.199 align:middle line:84%
I met quite a lot of people like
that in Europe, not in the US,

00:34:53.199 --> 00:34:55.300 align:middle line:84%
but in Europe,
interestingly enough.

00:34:55.300 --> 00:34:58.670 align:middle line:84%
So how to deal with
those situations

00:34:58.670 --> 00:35:02.170 align:middle line:84%
when you really have to
listen also deeply inside

00:35:02.170 --> 00:35:05.050 align:middle line:84%
for your own guidance
and not be lured

00:35:05.050 --> 00:35:10.090 align:middle line:84%
by what a seemingly
outside guru can give you?

00:35:10.090 --> 00:35:12.770 align:middle line:84%
These are very-- to me, these
are very, very important

00:35:12.770 --> 00:35:15.050 align:middle line:84%
questions right
now, because we are

00:35:15.050 --> 00:35:18.426 align:middle line:84%
sometimes following the wrong
people, and this-- yeah.

00:35:18.426 --> 00:35:20.520 align:middle line:84%
So I would love to
have your take on that,

00:35:20.520 --> 00:35:22.850 align:middle line:84%
within-- it's a little
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:35:22.850 --> 00:35:24.840 align:middle line:90%
within the conversation.

00:35:24.840 --> 00:35:27.330 align:middle line:84%
No, it's timely,
because when I first

00:35:27.330 --> 00:35:30.870 align:middle line:84%
started doing the work that
I was doing in helping people

00:35:30.870 --> 00:35:35.330 align:middle line:84%
and coaching them,
I realized actually,

00:35:35.330 --> 00:35:37.880 align:middle line:84%
I could spend a
lot of time helping

00:35:37.880 --> 00:35:42.000 align:middle line:84%
other people through
the things I'd mastered.

00:35:42.000 --> 00:35:43.900 align:middle line:84%
And I never called
myself a master.

00:35:43.900 --> 00:35:46.230 align:middle line:84%
I always said, as
Bruce Lee said,

00:35:46.230 --> 00:35:49.230 align:middle line:84%
I think we're all
student masters.

00:35:49.230 --> 00:35:51.810 align:middle line:90%
We're all training in mastery.

00:35:51.810 --> 00:35:54.720 align:middle line:84%
And that also means
that anybody is capable,

00:35:54.720 --> 00:35:57.690 align:middle line:84%
you know, of developing
mastery in their lives.

00:35:57.690 --> 00:35:58.890 align:middle line:90%
And my goal became that.

00:35:58.890 --> 00:36:01.340 align:middle line:84%
It became, how do
I help other people

00:36:01.340 --> 00:36:03.660 align:middle line:90%
to become their own masters?

00:36:03.660 --> 00:36:08.210 align:middle line:84%
Not to seek a master, but
to become their own master.

00:36:08.210 --> 00:36:10.270 align:middle line:84%
And each of us are on a
unique journey, each of us

00:36:10.270 --> 00:36:11.980 align:middle line:84%
have got unique
challenges in our lives,

00:36:11.980 --> 00:36:14.370 align:middle line:84%
and there's a
unique path that we

00:36:14.370 --> 00:36:17.370 align:middle line:84%
have to master in order for
us to fulfill our purpose

00:36:17.370 --> 00:36:20.060 align:middle line:84%
and for our gifts to make
a difference in the world.

00:36:20.060 --> 00:36:21.950 align:middle line:84%
So our challenge
in life is really,

00:36:21.950 --> 00:36:26.190 align:middle line:84%
how do we achieve mastery
over our own purpose

00:36:26.190 --> 00:36:30.010 align:middle line:84%
and our own fulfillment
of that purpose.

00:36:30.010 --> 00:36:32.360 align:middle line:84%
And that's-- that is the
biggest challenge of all.

00:36:32.360 --> 00:36:34.530 align:middle line:84%
Rather than running around
chasing after other people

00:36:34.530 --> 00:36:37.440 align:middle line:84%
who've only got half the
answer or part of the answer,

00:36:37.440 --> 00:36:41.210 align:middle line:84%
the only person who's got
all of the answer is you.

00:36:41.210 --> 00:36:46.970 align:middle line:84%
Now, in order to get to a place
where you begin to have mastery

00:36:46.970 --> 00:36:49.170 align:middle line:84%
over your own journey,
over your own path,

00:36:49.170 --> 00:36:52.750 align:middle line:84%
and when you act as your own
advisor, and you get to a point

00:36:52.750 --> 00:36:55.610 align:middle line:84%
where you don't borrow wisdom
any more from other people,

00:36:55.610 --> 00:36:58.140 align:middle line:84%
but you actually start to
get to generate your own,

00:36:58.140 --> 00:37:00.730 align:middle line:84%
that's probably the
most critical task

00:37:00.730 --> 00:37:03.500 align:middle line:84%
you've got to do
in terms of being

00:37:03.500 --> 00:37:05.540 align:middle line:90%
in a state your own mastery.

00:37:05.540 --> 00:37:08.690 align:middle line:84%
Now, some of you,
some of your viewers

00:37:08.690 --> 00:37:12.060 align:middle line:84%
may have heard the phrase,
that if you give a man a fish,

00:37:12.060 --> 00:37:15.060 align:middle line:84%
he gets to eat for a day, if you
give a man the ability to fish,

00:37:15.060 --> 00:37:16.880 align:middle line:84%
he can feed himself
and his family

00:37:16.880 --> 00:37:18.110 align:middle line:90%
for the rest of his life.

00:37:18.110 --> 00:37:20.525 align:middle line:84%
And I took that
particular phrase

00:37:20.525 --> 00:37:23.360 align:middle line:84%
and I changed it a
little bit for the sake

00:37:23.360 --> 00:37:24.940 align:middle line:90%
of mastery and wisdom.

00:37:24.940 --> 00:37:28.810 align:middle line:84%
And I said, you give
a person a wisdom

00:37:28.810 --> 00:37:32.020 align:middle line:84%
and he'll become
wise about one thing.

00:37:32.020 --> 00:37:36.440 align:middle line:84%
If you give a person the ability
to generate their own wisdom,

00:37:36.440 --> 00:37:39.380 align:middle line:84%
then they'll become
wise about everything.

00:37:39.380 --> 00:37:41.760 align:middle line:84%
However, if you give
a person the ability

